WEBVTT

00:12.480 --> 00:14.747
[ Down-tempo piano notes
            playing ]

00:34.668 --> 00:37.369
PEOPLE:
  [ Singsong ] Trick or treat!

00:37.371 --> 00:39.438
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

00:39.440 --> 00:41.607
[ Indistinct conversations ]

00:50.084 --> 00:51.617
[ Children shrieking ]

01:18.312 --> 01:21.547
CHILDREN:
        Happy Halloween!

01:21.549 --> 01:23.649
[ <i> Mid-tempo rock music playing</i> ]

01:31.725 --> 01:34.326
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:36.330 --> 01:39.598
MAN: Man, I see what
    you're doing over there.

01:42.403 --> 01:43.735
You're up, right?

01:43.737 --> 01:47.239
TROY: Come on, hostess.
         It's your play.

01:47.241 --> 01:50.809
CHERYL: I feel like
         it's your turn.

01:50.811 --> 01:52.544
-MAN: Horny devil.
       -CHERYL: Yeah.

01:52.546 --> 01:54.880
TROY:
    I think Cheryl should go.

01:56.450 --> 01:59.418
Who will I meet tonight?

01:59.720 --> 02:02.721
-MAN: [ Howls ]
        -WOMAN: Oh ho!

02:02.723 --> 02:05.591
MAN:
       All right, Cheryl!

02:11.298 --> 02:14.333
[ All howling ]

02:16.203 --> 02:17.903
-Stop.
           -[ Laughs ]

02:21.609 --> 02:23.742
TROY:
      I'm telling your mom!

02:24.912 --> 02:26.411
Yo, yo.
       Group up, group up.

02:26.413 --> 02:28.714
Everyone say,
      "Troy's number one."

02:28.716 --> 02:30.916
ALL:
       Troy's an asshole!

02:30.918 --> 02:32.384
MAN: [ Laughs ]

02:32.386 --> 02:34.720
Yeah, yeah.
     Laugh it up, fuckfaces.

02:34.722 --> 02:36.255
Who's next?
            Come on.

02:36.257 --> 02:38.157
It's your turn, Trick.

02:38.159 --> 02:41.827
Trick. Trickster.
         Let's go, man.

02:41.829 --> 02:43.929
-Let's see it, pumpkinhead.
   -NICKY: Come on, Trick.

02:57.178 --> 02:59.178
-[ Cheering ]
          -MAN: Oh, no!

02:59.180 --> 03:01.446
[ Laughter ]

03:01.448 --> 03:03.182
Let's go.

03:03.184 --> 03:05.217
It's your lucky night.

03:06.520 --> 03:08.887
-No! No re-spins.
       -It's just a kiss.

03:08.889 --> 03:10.422
Just get it over with.

03:10.424 --> 03:12.224
Don't be chickenshit, man.

03:12.226 --> 03:15.227
Do it with a guy, Trick!
              Yeah!

03:16.197 --> 03:18.363
TROY: Come on, hey.
      What's he doing now?

03:18.365 --> 03:19.831
MAN: If it feels good do it,
             Trick.

03:19.833 --> 03:23.202
Hey! Lose the mask
    if you're gonna kiss him.

03:23.204 --> 03:24.903
What is he doing?

03:24.905 --> 03:26.638
I'll get
      out of the way here.

03:26.640 --> 03:28.340
TROY: Let's give him a little
      motivation here, huh?

03:28.342 --> 03:29.775
Slow clap for Trick?

03:29.777 --> 03:32.778
ALL: [ Chanting ] Trick! Trick!
          Trick! Trick!

03:32.780 --> 03:34.580
Trick! Trick! Trick!

03:34.582 --> 03:36.782
Trick! Trick! Trick!
          Trick! Trick!

03:36.784 --> 03:38.450
Trick! Trick! Trick!
      Trick! Trick! Trick!

03:38.452 --> 03:39.985
Trick! Trick! Trick!
      Trick! Trick! Trick!

03:39.987 --> 03:41.954
Trick! Trick! Trick! Trick!
      Trick! Trick! Trick!

03:41.956 --> 03:44.890
Trick! Trick! Trick! Trick!
      Trick! Trick! Trick!

03:48.829 --> 03:50.429
[ Grunting ]

03:54.935 --> 03:57.636
CHERYL: Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
          Are you okay?

04:03.344 --> 04:05.310
WOMAN:
          Let go of me!

04:17.625 --> 04:19.958
Stop!
             Please!

04:21.394 --> 04:23.528
Stop!
              Stop!

04:28.369 --> 04:29.501
MAN:
         Get him, Troy!

04:29.503 --> 04:31.270
You fucking psycho!

04:31.272 --> 04:32.571
Shit!

04:32.573 --> 04:34.539
[ Indistinct shouting
         and screaming ]

04:40.914 --> 04:42.381
[ Slashing ]

04:48.656 --> 04:49.788
No!

04:57.765 --> 04:59.331
Get off!

05:01.769 --> 05:03.368
MAN: Help!

05:11.712 --> 05:13.912
[ Stabbing ]

05:21.021 --> 05:24.022
[ Whimpering ]

05:24.024 --> 05:25.424
TROY: Trick!

05:25.426 --> 05:27.025
[ Thud ]

05:56.824 --> 06:00.892
You batshit-fucking-crazy
         son of a bitch.

06:27.454 --> 06:29.755
[ <i> Indistinct conversation</i>
           <i> echoing</i> ]

06:33.026 --> 06:35.427
-Hey.
           -Hey, Mike.

06:35.429 --> 06:37.129
Thanks for coming.
    I know it's a long drive.

06:37.131 --> 06:41.099
But they're gonna question
   my every move on this one.

06:42.736 --> 06:44.469
Did you tell them
   that you're the only cadet

06:44.471 --> 06:46.405
I ever learned
       a few things from?

06:46.407 --> 06:48.540
Like that'll matter.

06:48.542 --> 06:50.142
Either way,
       I'm happy to help.

06:50.144 --> 06:53.011
You say that now.

06:53.747 --> 06:56.114
[ Indistinct conversations ]

07:09.496 --> 07:11.863
DENVER: Why does he have
  that shit all over his face?

07:11.865 --> 07:12.898
JAYNE:
    It was a Halloween party.

07:12.900 --> 07:14.566
Okay, why does he <i> still</i>

07:14.568 --> 07:15.901
have that shit
       all over his face?

07:16.804 --> 07:18.670
They were more concerned
      with saving his life

07:18.672 --> 07:19.704
than washing his face.

07:20.741 --> 07:22.140
So this Patrick Weaver,

07:22.142 --> 07:24.476
he killed four seniors
      at a Halloween party?

07:24.478 --> 07:28.680
Five.
   Fifth just died in surgery.

07:28.682 --> 07:32.050
Four more injured,
          two critical.

07:32.052 --> 07:34.920
One, Troy Meeks --
   junior, football captain --

07:34.922 --> 07:37.889
stabbed Patrick
     with a fireplace poker.

07:37.891 --> 07:40.459
Were it not for Troy,
    there would be more dead.

07:40.461 --> 07:42.127
He's 18 with no priors?

07:42.129 --> 07:43.628
CHERYL:
       Trick killed Evan.

07:45.132 --> 07:49.601
And Dan and Tammy and Parker.

07:49.603 --> 07:52.170
-Trick?
            -Patrick.

07:52.172 --> 07:54.940
E-Everyone calls him Trick.

07:56.577 --> 07:58.610
DENVER: Did he have a beef
      with the other kids?

07:58.612 --> 08:01.213
He didn't have beef
       with anyone. He...

08:01.215 --> 08:04.483
He was quiet.
             Smart.

08:04.485 --> 08:06.585
So he was bullied.

08:06.587 --> 08:08.720
Um...

08:08.722 --> 08:10.088
No, he...

08:16.763 --> 08:19.164
No, no.
       Not that I know of.

08:19.166 --> 08:21.766
He...

08:21.768 --> 08:25.237
He used to help people
      with their homework.

08:27.541 --> 08:31.643
You should go.
   I'll be in touch tomorrow.

08:31.645 --> 08:33.645
Can I see Nicky?

08:33.647 --> 08:35.614
Yeah.
         She's upstairs.

08:38.885 --> 08:40.619
We're trying to
        find his parents.

08:40.621 --> 08:41.919
As soon as we do,
      you can talk to them.

08:41.922 --> 08:43.989
Well, he's 18,
     so parental permission,

08:43.991 --> 08:45.257
it's a courtesy.

08:45.259 --> 08:47.092
This kid
     in the big leagues now.

08:47.094 --> 08:49.561
And I'm betting that he's got
     a date with death row.

08:53.233 --> 08:55.000
[ Door opens ]

08:55.002 --> 08:56.868
Hey, how you doing?

08:56.870 --> 08:58.937
JAYNE: Deputy Green,
    this is Detective Denver.

08:58.939 --> 09:00.739
We go back a ways.

09:00.741 --> 09:02.807
DENVER: Could you grab us
    a couple coffees, please?

09:02.809 --> 09:04.242
And take this.

09:06.280 --> 09:07.612
How is he?

09:07.614 --> 09:09.581
Hell of a scar
         in his future,

09:09.583 --> 09:10.916
but with a little bit of luck,

09:10.918 --> 09:12.584
he'll be back on his feet
           in no time.

09:12.586 --> 09:13.818
DENVER:
     Give us a minute, Doc?

09:16.924 --> 09:19.925
I know they said this kid
    did some terrible things,

09:19.927 --> 09:21.993
but do I need to remind him
           his rights?

09:21.995 --> 09:23.595
No.

09:26.767 --> 09:30.835
Patrick, you already know
       Sheriff Lisa Jayne.

09:30.837 --> 09:33.939
And, look, I heard
       you're a good kid.

09:33.941 --> 09:35.774
What made you
        lose it tonight?

09:35.776 --> 09:38.076
Were you provoked?

09:38.078 --> 09:40.712
Did you feel threatened?

09:40.714 --> 09:41.880
Were those kids
          bullying you?

09:47.187 --> 09:50.755
Hey, can we get somebody to come
  wipe this crap off his face?

09:50.757 --> 09:52.624
I'd like to see
       who I'm talking to.

09:52.626 --> 09:53.959
Of course.

09:54.861 --> 09:57.195
-[ Door closes ]
 -Kid, you got to work with me.

09:57.197 --> 09:58.897
If you want my help,

09:58.899 --> 10:01.166
you got to tell me
     your side of the story.

10:06.306 --> 10:07.872
This isn't gonna do.

10:07.874 --> 10:09.708
And the strong, silent types,

10:09.710 --> 10:11.076
they don't last long
           in prison.

10:12.779 --> 10:15.246
And I got to tell you, you're
  looking at more than life --

10:24.291 --> 10:26.691
[ Slashing ]

10:38.972 --> 10:41.206
Help him out, Doc.

10:41.208 --> 10:43.808
Which way did he go?
          You see him?

10:45.212 --> 10:47.679
-JAYNE: Oh, God.
        -Let's get him.

10:53.820 --> 10:56.021
Hey.
         Come here, kid!

11:13.874 --> 11:15.040
Hey!

11:16.243 --> 11:17.275
Come here, kid!

11:20.013 --> 11:21.413
Let her go.

11:22.816 --> 11:25.350
-Hey. Stop.
    -JAYNE: Come on, Patrick.

11:25.352 --> 11:26.985
Don't do it.

11:26.987 --> 11:29.354
Don't do it.

11:29.356 --> 11:31.189
JAYNE:
           It's over.

11:34.294 --> 11:36.394
-[ Thud ]
           -[ Gasps ]

11:36.930 --> 11:38.863
[ Gunfire ]

11:43.003 --> 11:44.703
[ Tires screeching ]

11:47.140 --> 11:49.741
[ Alarms buzzing ]

11:49.743 --> 11:51.376
-Fuck.
            -Come on.

11:51.378 --> 11:53.945
-You okay?
           -Come on!

11:58.752 --> 12:01.352
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

12:01.354 --> 12:03.888
[ Grunting ]

12:03.890 --> 12:05.190
No, no, no, no.

12:05.192 --> 12:06.925
Hey, did you see him?
         Where'd he go?

12:06.927 --> 12:08.960
Of course I saw him, shithead.
      That's why I swerved.

12:08.962 --> 12:10.895
Did you see him get up?

12:10.897 --> 12:12.163
JAYNE:
            Oh, look.

12:13.967 --> 12:15.467
This way.

12:21.108 --> 12:22.407
Here!

12:25.045 --> 12:28.246
Ah, shit.
       He's in the river.

12:29.950 --> 12:31.850
I've never seen
       anything like that.

12:31.852 --> 12:34.786
-How's he still alive?
     -He isn't.

12:35.455 --> 12:37.422
We put at least
      three bullets in him.

12:37.424 --> 12:39.457
He fell two stories.

12:39.459 --> 12:41.893
Look at how much blood
            he lost.

12:41.895 --> 12:43.862
You saw his arm.
    He can't swim like that.

12:43.864 --> 12:46.264
He'll drown,
       if not hypothermia.

12:46.266 --> 12:48.066
He's probably already dead.

12:48.068 --> 12:50.101
You saw it, right?
            His eyes?

12:50.103 --> 12:53.037
-Saw what?
   -He was getting off on it.

12:55.408 --> 12:57.275
He isn't anymore.

12:58.178 --> 12:59.878
Trick Weaver is dead.

12:59.880 --> 13:03.081
We'll set up a perimeter,
   but I doubt we'll find him.

13:05.919 --> 13:08.920
This is Sheriff Jayne.
       I need K9 units...

13:21.168 --> 13:24.202
From interviewing
  fellow students, teachers --

13:24.204 --> 13:27.172
"Trick was so quiet.
      He'd never do that."

13:27.174 --> 13:29.440
The old "quiet one" cliché.

13:29.442 --> 13:33.111
JAYNE: "Trick was," and I quote,
         "smart as fuck.

13:33.113 --> 13:35.079
Always made more sense
       than the teachers."

13:35.081 --> 13:37.382
Ever get in trouble? Suspension,
      detention, anything?

13:37.384 --> 13:39.150
Too smart to get in trouble.

13:39.152 --> 13:41.286
History teacher of 27 years

13:41.288 --> 13:45.423
stated Trick often made
 the teachers feel incompetent.

13:45.425 --> 13:47.091
What do we have to do
  to get a picture of this kid?

13:47.093 --> 13:49.861
No Facebook,
    no Instagram, no Twitter.

13:49.863 --> 13:52.163
If he used social media,
        he was anonymous.

13:52.165 --> 13:54.132
WAN: Weaver skipped
        his class photo.

13:54.134 --> 13:55.867
We asked the annual staff
     to check the database,

13:55.869 --> 13:57.202
see if they had any candids.

13:57.204 --> 13:58.603
We also made an announcement
        to the students,

13:58.605 --> 14:00.839
see if anybody had any photos
        on their phones.

14:00.841 --> 14:02.307
So far, we got nothing.

14:02.309 --> 14:04.242
This is all they have
   before the video cuts off.

14:04.244 --> 14:06.911
No footage of Trick getting up
      or leaving the scene.

14:06.913 --> 14:09.047
There's no shadow movement.

14:13.019 --> 14:15.119
NICKY:
      Really thin eyebrows.

14:17.190 --> 14:18.356
Thin lips.

14:18.358 --> 14:21.359
No.
           Thick lips.

14:21.361 --> 14:22.493
TROY:
          Skinny face.

14:22.495 --> 14:24.195
Kind of
      a hollowed-out face.

14:24.197 --> 14:26.998
Black, roughed-up hair.

14:27.000 --> 14:29.167
-Scruffy.
         -Deep-set eyes.

14:29.169 --> 14:30.335
He had green eyes.

14:30.337 --> 14:32.537
-Beady.
           -Blue eyes.

14:32.539 --> 14:36.007
CHERYL: Just really
       kind-looking eyes.

14:42.249 --> 14:44.115
He could be anybody.

14:44.117 --> 14:46.351
NICKY: I saw him eyeing Trick
    one day, and I was like,

14:46.353 --> 14:47.886
"You planning
     on messing with Trick?"

14:47.888 --> 14:50.421
Then Trick,
   who had to be 50 yards away

14:50.423 --> 14:53.591
sitting at a picnic table,
  turns and stares right at us.

14:53.593 --> 14:57.061
No way he could've heard me.
    Hell, we both went pale.

14:57.063 --> 14:58.997
Troy was like, "Nah, man.
  I ain't messing with Trick."

14:58.999 --> 15:00.531
And Troy messed
         with everybody.

15:00.533 --> 15:03.234
JAYNE: We're wondering
     if Patrick was bullied,

15:03.236 --> 15:05.670
and we heard you might be
       the man to talk to.

15:05.672 --> 15:08.172
TROY: No, no, I don't know who's
 been shooting their mouth off.

15:08.174 --> 15:09.941
I ain't no bully.

15:09.943 --> 15:12.110
Maybe I get a little rough,
   but I never touched Trick.

15:12.112 --> 15:15.680
Not him.
  Until, you know, he lost it.

15:15.682 --> 15:17.615
I saw there was a fire poker
      next to the fireplace

15:17.617 --> 15:19.384
when I was there,
        so I just, like,

15:19.386 --> 15:21.019
just one of those
        animal instinct,

15:21.021 --> 15:22.520
just clean shot,
     just right in the gut.

15:22.522 --> 15:24.389
I was dressed up
         as a superhero.

15:24.391 --> 15:26.624
Little did I know you have to
  become the hero of the night.

15:26.626 --> 15:29.127
I saved a lot of people.

15:29.129 --> 15:30.328
Me.

15:30.330 --> 15:32.463
He was sweet, you know?

15:32.465 --> 15:35.166
I still can't believe
         what happened.

15:35.168 --> 15:36.567
What about his folks?

15:36.569 --> 15:38.636
Did they know
        he was like this?

15:38.638 --> 15:43.541
Or did they make him
            this way?

15:55.021 --> 15:56.220
JAYNE:
  According to school records,

15:56.222 --> 15:58.556
this is
    Patrick Weaver's address.

15:58.558 --> 16:00.124
Barge hasn't moved
         in five years.

16:00.126 --> 16:01.693
We don't know
    where he actually lived.

16:01.695 --> 16:04.195
We don't even know if
 Patrick Weaver's his real name.

16:04.197 --> 16:06.097
DENVER:
   How is that even possible?

16:06.099 --> 16:07.999
Kid goes to a school
        for a whole year,

16:08.001 --> 16:10.134
and no one checks his address?

16:10.136 --> 16:12.670
-No one ever met his parents?
  -JAYNE: E-mails.

16:12.672 --> 16:14.706
Teachers spoke
  with both parents by e-mail.

16:14.708 --> 16:16.541
DENVER: E-mails?

16:18.178 --> 16:21.312
Denver,
     it's been three weeks.

16:21.314 --> 16:23.214
I'm starting
      to get some pressure.

16:23.216 --> 16:26.451
There's too many unanswered
  questions to close this case.

16:26.453 --> 16:28.086
And when were you gonna
          tell me about

16:28.088 --> 16:30.021
the two-faced pumpkin mask?

16:30.023 --> 16:31.456
Who told you about that?

16:31.458 --> 16:33.057
The mask was stolen
   from your evidence locker,

16:33.059 --> 16:34.525
and you don't
       bother to tell me?

16:34.527 --> 16:36.094
Because you would
       assume it was him.

16:36.096 --> 16:38.696
-Of course I would.
     -Trick Weaver is dead.

16:38.698 --> 16:40.999
Show me the body,
      and I'll believe it.

16:42.602 --> 16:44.168
I'm not saying
       I'll quit looking,

16:44.170 --> 16:46.604
but, Mike,
    I got to put my resources

16:46.606 --> 16:49.307
back on a county
      that's been ignored.

16:54.114 --> 16:57.582
¶ Here comes the night ¶

16:57.584 --> 17:03.521
¶ Everything will be
           all right ¶

17:03.523 --> 17:10.028
¶ Can you feel
      the shining sound? ¶

17:10.030 --> 17:13.431
¶ It's just my heart ¶

17:13.433 --> 17:15.133
[ Rapping ] ¶ Let her
         in my dreams ¶

17:15.135 --> 17:16.768
¶ She was my queen ¶

17:16.770 --> 17:19.337
¶ A castle in the mountaintops,
      rivers, and streams ¶

17:19.339 --> 17:21.638
¶ Plucking sunlight
   from the sky in my pocket ¶

17:21.641 --> 17:24.675
¶ Give it to you later on
    in the form of a locket ¶

17:24.676 --> 17:27.111
¶ People in the back,
  for the people in the front ¶

17:27.113 --> 17:28.445
¶ For the people on the side ¶

17:28.448 --> 17:29.647
¶ For the people
         want to front ¶

17:29.649 --> 17:30.815
¶ For the people in the back ¶

17:30.817 --> 17:32.316
¶ For the people in the front ¶

17:32.318 --> 17:33.651
¶ For the people on the side ¶

17:33.653 --> 17:35.453
¶ For the people want to front ¶

17:35.455 --> 17:38.156
¶ And all around town,
   people trying to get down ¶

17:38.158 --> 17:41.325
¶ And all around town,
   people trying to get down ¶

17:41.327 --> 17:43.594
-[ Indistinct conversations ]
  -[ Dance music playing ]

18:06.286 --> 18:07.785
[ Knife sliding ]

18:15.695 --> 18:18.096
MAN:
         Check this out.

18:18.098 --> 18:21.199
Who is this guy?

18:21.201 --> 18:23.301
WOMAN: What the hell
     are you supposed to be?

18:25.839 --> 18:27.438
-[ Gasping ]
         -[ Screaming ]

18:51.431 --> 18:53.231
[ Gasping ]

18:53.233 --> 18:54.499
MAN:
          Stupid kids.

19:04.144 --> 19:07.145
[ Stabbing ]

19:15.355 --> 19:17.255
[ Slashes ]

19:23.830 --> 19:25.696
DENVER: Six dead,
         three injured.

19:25.698 --> 19:27.198
No one could I.D. him.

19:27.200 --> 19:28.599
They're not even sure
         he's a student,

19:28.601 --> 19:30.735
but witnesses say
      his face was painted.

19:32.338 --> 19:35.673
You don't really believe
           it's Trick.

19:35.675 --> 19:37.175
We never found a body.

19:37.177 --> 19:39.944
-W-We shot him, Mike.
      -Yeah, we did.

19:39.946 --> 19:41.646
But don't you think
    it's curious that our guy

19:41.648 --> 19:43.548
vanished into the river
    after killing five teens,

19:43.550 --> 19:46.617
and a year later six teens
  are killed on the same river?

19:46.619 --> 19:48.553
Do you think
        he floated there?

19:48.555 --> 19:51.322
-[ Cellphone beeps ]
      -I got to take this.

20:00.533 --> 20:03.601
JAYNE: Everyone wants the
   monster to live in the end.

20:03.603 --> 20:05.770
Why is that?

