41:11.636 --> 41:13.169
[ Groaning ]

41:13.171 --> 41:15.138
What the hell is that?

41:15.140 --> 41:16.539
JAYNE: Doesn't matter.
          It's just...

41:16.541 --> 41:18.107
Got to just get you
        to the hospital.

41:18.109 --> 41:19.709
I got you, I got you.

41:25.951 --> 41:27.016
Keep talking, Green.

41:27.018 --> 41:29.686
Tell me about something.

41:29.688 --> 41:31.187
I met a girl.

41:31.189 --> 41:33.556
A girl, huh?

41:33.558 --> 41:36.659
Do tell.
    But do it while we drive.

41:45.737 --> 41:47.070
Oh, no, no.
              Shit!

41:48.039 --> 41:50.173
Shit. Get out!
   Get out, get out, get out!

42:02.621 --> 42:05.255
Oh, fucking God.

42:11.229 --> 42:13.963
Chickenshit!
         I'm right here!

42:21.840 --> 42:23.806
[ Water splashes ]

42:37.689 --> 42:41.024
It's Trick.
           Has to be.

42:41.026 --> 42:45.595
Internet said he was back.
         Psycho's viral.

42:45.597 --> 42:46.729
He did this.

42:46.731 --> 42:48.298
He did not.
         Weaver's dead.

42:48.300 --> 42:50.700
-This is a copycat.
       -Yeah?

42:50.702 --> 42:52.902
-WAN: Yeah.
      -Maybe you're right.

42:52.904 --> 42:56.806
But where's Denver?
        Maybe he did it.

42:56.808 --> 42:59.108
Trick follows him
      like a shadow, right?

42:59.110 --> 43:00.677
Maybe Denver's Trick.

43:01.313 --> 43:05.148
Shut the fuck up, Slater.
          Do your job.

43:05.150 --> 43:06.816
-Come on, rookie.
        -Sorry, Sheriff.

43:06.818 --> 43:08.851
-Come on.
           -Sheriff...

43:08.853 --> 43:11.020
-I shouldn't have said that.
  -Let's go.

43:29.140 --> 43:31.307
I'm so sorry.

43:34.012 --> 43:36.179
Keep thinking I'll wake up.

43:37.716 --> 43:39.315
He was a good kid.

43:41.219 --> 43:43.152
This is one of the feds

43:43.154 --> 43:45.121
that got killed
        last year, right?

43:46.057 --> 43:47.991
Reason you lost your badge?

43:49.728 --> 43:51.928
Yeah.

43:51.930 --> 43:53.129
He's trying to
        make a statement.

43:53.131 --> 43:54.864
Trying?

43:54.866 --> 43:56.833
He's made
  his fucking statement, Mike.

43:56.835 --> 44:00.670
-Green is dead.
         -I know that.

44:00.672 --> 44:03.172
This...

44:03.174 --> 44:04.941
This is beyond abnormal.

44:04.943 --> 44:07.276
What does that even mean?

44:07.278 --> 44:09.145
He murdered your deputy
        with a gravestone

44:09.147 --> 44:11.180
of a fed I got killed.

44:11.182 --> 44:13.216
Who does that?

44:13.218 --> 44:15.652
<i> What</i> does that?

44:18.690 --> 44:20.056
Look...

44:20.058 --> 44:22.025
I've never been a believer.

44:22.027 --> 44:25.862
Ghosts, Bigfoot, aliens.
           God, Satan.

44:25.864 --> 44:27.830
I believe what I can see
      and what I can touch.

44:27.832 --> 44:29.999
But this...

44:31.269 --> 44:33.102
This?

44:34.939 --> 44:37.106
This is pure evil.

44:37.108 --> 44:40.276
That kid
is goddamn darkness personified.

44:40.278 --> 44:42.311
I told you,
      I believe it's Trick,

44:42.313 --> 44:45.248
but don't expect me
   to jump on the devil wagon.

44:47.152 --> 44:48.851
A curfew won't work,
            will it?

44:51.356 --> 44:53.389
Maybe if I leave town,
          he'll follow.

44:53.391 --> 44:55.258
I'll lead him
         away from here.

44:55.260 --> 44:57.460
No, he's past that,
        and you know it.

44:57.462 --> 45:00.730
He's marked his territory.
    He's made his challenge.

45:00.732 --> 45:02.732
So, what do you suggest?

45:04.135 --> 45:06.936
I know a place we can go.

45:06.938 --> 45:08.438
Somewhere we control.

45:08.440 --> 45:12.742
And when he comes for us,
          evil or not,

45:12.744 --> 45:14.744
we'll make sure he doesn't
      walk away this time.

45:18.750 --> 45:20.249
Smooth Jonny
          in the house!

45:20.251 --> 45:23.119
-Whoo!
          -There we go.

45:23.121 --> 45:24.320
Yo, I know you're not...

45:24.322 --> 45:25.955
-Hey, there he is.
       -Give me that.

45:25.957 --> 45:27.290
Forgot about Nicky, man.

45:27.292 --> 45:30.393
She a real piece of work.
         That shit nuts.

45:30.395 --> 45:33.262
Hey.
        To Trick Weaver.

45:34.866 --> 45:36.733
I'm glad you're dead!
           [ Laughs ]

45:36.735 --> 45:39.902
-ALL: Yeah!
          -[ Laughter ]

45:39.904 --> 45:42.004
And -- And -- And...

45:42.006 --> 45:43.806
And here's to Troy.

45:43.808 --> 45:46.275
The man, the myth, the legend.

45:46.277 --> 45:51.013
Skewered
 the Benton High School slasher.

45:51.015 --> 45:52.815
To the hero.

45:52.817 --> 45:54.183
To the man!

45:54.185 --> 45:56.519
To Troy?!

45:56.521 --> 45:58.054
To Troy!

45:58.056 --> 46:00.857
[ Cheering ]

46:01.960 --> 46:03.259
Yo, quick.
        Shut up, hold up.

46:03.261 --> 46:04.460
REPORTER:
  <i> Could this be Trick Weaver?</i>

46:04.462 --> 46:06.229
JAYNE:
     <i> Trick Weaver is dead.</i>

46:06.231 --> 46:08.064
REPORTER: <i> But, Sheriff,</i>
     <i> your deputy was killed</i>

46:08.066 --> 46:10.333
<i> with the gravestone</i>
 <i> of federal agent Tina Mendez,</i>

46:10.335 --> 46:13.069
<i> the agent whose death</i>
  <i> led to Mike Denver's firing,</i>

46:13.071 --> 46:15.838
<i> and now we have sources</i>
<i> informing us that Denver's name</i>

46:15.840 --> 46:17.406
<i> was written in blood</i>
       <i> at the rest stop.</i>

46:17.408 --> 46:18.808
JAYNE:
         <i> What sources?</i>

46:18.810 --> 46:21.344
REPORTER:
     <i> So you don't deny it?</i>

46:21.346 --> 46:25.348
JAYNE: <i> Like I said,</i>
     <i> Trick Weaver is dead.</i>

46:28.987 --> 46:31.988
TROY: What?
             Chill.

46:31.990 --> 46:34.090
The dude's dead.
            Trust me.

46:34.092 --> 46:36.559
I don't know, man.
      Never found the body.

46:36.561 --> 46:38.494
Trick Weaver could still be
    coming back for you, man.

46:38.496 --> 46:40.229
-No, man.
       -No, no, what if --

46:40.231 --> 46:42.265
-What if -- Shit...
       -Trick's dead, yo.

46:42.267 --> 46:44.267
I'm telling you.
        I'm telling you.

46:44.269 --> 46:46.869
So you're not worried
             at all?

46:46.871 --> 46:48.504
-Ha!
            -No way.

46:48.506 --> 46:51.274
Not just a little bit?

46:52.377 --> 46:55.411
Just get another bottle
       and hit Talbott's?

46:55.413 --> 46:56.946
Fuckin' A.
           Halloween.

46:56.948 --> 46:59.115
-Hell yeah.
     -Keep this party going?

46:59.117 --> 47:01.818
Old man Talbott's
   Halloween horror marathon.

47:01.820 --> 47:03.219
What?!
             What?!

47:03.221 --> 47:04.487
Blood and guts
      from dusk till dawn!

47:04.489 --> 47:06.222
[ Cheering ]

47:06.224 --> 47:09.258
ALL: Blood and guts!
 Blood and guts! Blood and guts!

47:09.260 --> 47:10.927
Let's go!

47:40.258 --> 47:41.457
DENVER: Why here?

47:41.459 --> 47:42.325
JAYNE:
   It's where it all started.

47:42.327 --> 47:43.993
Plus the place is empty.

47:43.995 --> 47:46.095
DENVER: Nobody bought it
  after Cheryl's family moved?

47:46.097 --> 47:47.496
JAYNE: Would you
       want to live here?

47:47.498 --> 47:48.965
DENVER:
      Would I want to live

47:48.967 --> 47:49.966
where this evil prick
         got his start?

47:49.968 --> 47:51.367
-Hard pass.
           -"Evil."

47:51.369 --> 47:53.102
Mike, you got to cut that word
        from your vocab.

47:53.104 --> 47:54.570
There is no evil.

47:54.572 --> 47:56.439
Look, forget my assumptions.
       Consider the facts.

47:56.441 --> 47:57.607
How many times
        did we shoot him?

47:57.609 --> 47:59.175
How many stories
          did he fall?

47:59.177 --> 48:00.376
How cold was that water?

48:00.378 --> 48:02.078
No family, no history,
           no future.

48:02.080 --> 48:04.180
And yet he's the poisonous fog
          that rolls in

48:04.182 --> 48:06.582
and kills everyone without
   rhyme, reason, or remorse.

48:06.584 --> 48:08.284
You're confusing evil
           with crazy.

48:08.286 --> 48:10.453
-[ Keys jingling ]
       -This isn't crazy.

48:10.455 --> 48:12.121
I know crazy.
         Cops are crazy.

48:12.123 --> 48:15.424
[ Chuckles ] You're right.
         Cops <i> are</i> crazy.

48:15.426 --> 48:19.161
But it's different 'cause
  we're not alone in our crazy.

48:19.163 --> 48:21.497
I play Tuesday-night hearts
           with cops.

48:21.499 --> 48:24.267
I eat with cops.
        I bowl with cops.

48:24.269 --> 48:25.468
I fuck cops.

48:25.470 --> 48:28.337
We may be crazy,
      but we're not alone.

48:28.339 --> 48:29.639
But Trick is.

48:29.641 --> 48:33.576
His crazy is alone
         and methodical.

48:33.578 --> 48:35.311
He can join a Nazi group
          on Facebook,

48:35.313 --> 48:38.481
even build his rep in the feeds,
       but not as himself.

48:38.483 --> 48:41.550
No, the only ones
       he shows himself to

48:41.552 --> 48:43.085
are those hunting him.

48:43.087 --> 48:46.055
He needs you.
             And me.

48:46.057 --> 48:49.325
The Internet isn't his audience.
             We are.

48:49.327 --> 48:53.296
So we stop believing
     and he just goes away?

48:53.298 --> 48:55.064
That type of thinking
       will get you dead.

48:55.066 --> 48:57.967
Oh, Trick is real.
     But think for a second.

48:57.969 --> 48:59.969
He's not always Trick,
             is he?

49:01.072 --> 49:02.939
Every day's not Halloween.

49:02.941 --> 49:05.241
What's he do
   when he's not taunting you?

49:06.444 --> 49:08.077
Take it slow.
      He could be in there.

49:08.079 --> 49:09.512
County pays
     for a security system.

49:09.514 --> 49:10.980
-[ Keypad beeping ]
     -No one can open a door

49:10.982 --> 49:13.115
or window without me
        knowing about it.

49:13.117 --> 49:15.318
[ Hinges creaking ]

49:17.288 --> 49:19.488
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

49:22.994 --> 49:25.261
What was that you said
   about getting ahead of him?

49:25.263 --> 49:27.697
Wan, I need you and Slater
     at Cheryl's old house.

49:27.699 --> 49:30.032
Now we know what he's doing
       in the off-season.

49:30.034 --> 49:32.168
WAN:
 Ten-four, Sheriff. On our way.

49:33.738 --> 49:35.705
I can't believe this kid
     was right under my nose

49:35.707 --> 49:38.174
and I never knew it.

49:39.310 --> 49:40.743
[ Gun cocks ]

49:40.745 --> 49:43.045
[ Music continues ]

50:00.131 --> 50:02.231
JAYNE:
      Talbott's barn door.

50:02.233 --> 50:03.599
You know in 40 years,

50:03.601 --> 50:05.668
Talbott only removed one name
        from this thing?

50:05.670 --> 50:07.069
[ Chuckles softly ]

50:07.071 --> 50:09.071
He's told the story often
             enough.

50:15.380 --> 50:18.414
Someone didn't
      want to be forgotten.

50:28.292 --> 50:30.793
[ Dramatic music plays ]

50:43.541 --> 50:47.743
Your windows and doors were
 alarmed, so he dug his way in.

50:48.679 --> 50:51.347
WAN:
    Sheriff, pulling up now.

50:51.349 --> 50:52.448
Copy that.

50:56.587 --> 50:58.320
-Deputy Wan, Slater.
      -SLATER: Sir.

50:58.322 --> 51:00.089
-Denver.
     -You sure he was here?

51:00.091 --> 51:02.091
-Yeah, he's been here.
  -And we think he'll be back.

51:02.093 --> 51:03.759
So I want you both to --

51:03.761 --> 51:05.694
Where's your SUV?

51:05.696 --> 51:08.164
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

51:10.468 --> 51:13.269
TALBOTT:
  Have I seen a kid in makeup?

51:13.271 --> 51:16.672
You're shitting me, right?
     They're all in makeup.

51:16.674 --> 51:19.108
It's goddamn Halloween,
         Deputy Reddick.

51:19.110 --> 51:22.144
Well, regardless, Sheriff wants
   eyes and ears here tonight.

51:22.146 --> 51:25.281
I got all the eyes and ears
      you need right here.

51:25.283 --> 51:27.349
But if I were you,

51:27.351 --> 51:30.686
I'd go around back,
       check out the maze.

51:30.688 --> 51:35.157
Folks tend to get rowdy when
   they've soiled their jeans.

51:35.159 --> 51:37.293
Okay, Mr. Talbott.
        I'll go do that.

51:37.295 --> 51:38.594
-Thank you.
           -All right.

51:39.697 --> 51:41.330
MAN:
            1025 APB.

51:41.332 --> 51:42.798
All units be on the lookout

51:42.800 --> 51:45.501
for the stolen 2010
      white Ford Expedition

51:45.503 --> 51:47.369
belonging to Mike Denver.

51:47.371 --> 51:49.805
[ Indistinct conversations,
     screaming in distance ]

51:49.807 --> 51:52.141
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

51:52.143 --> 51:53.776
[ Animal growling ]

51:53.778 --> 51:55.578
GIRL:
             Scary.

51:55.580 --> 51:57.313
-CHERYL: Are you excited?
    -GREG: Yeah.

51:57.315 --> 51:59.281
CHERYL:
   I'm gonna grab the tickets.

51:59.283 --> 52:01.450
[ Animal howling ]

52:03.888 --> 52:05.788
Greg!
            Come on!

52:05.790 --> 52:08.157
You're never gonna see
           that movie!

52:10.228 --> 52:12.661
He does not listen.

52:14.565 --> 52:18.134
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

52:20.138 --> 52:21.470
GREG:
            Oh, stop.

52:21.472 --> 52:23.572
You told Cheryl you've seen this
        a hundred times.

52:23.574 --> 52:24.907
Why can't I see it once?

52:24.909 --> 52:26.675
I don't want to see it one time.

52:26.677 --> 52:28.144
You want to be scared?

52:28.146 --> 52:30.446
The maze is where
    the real monsters are --

52:30.448 --> 52:31.780
not some dumb movie.

52:31.782 --> 52:33.582
I don't want to be scared
            neither.

52:33.584 --> 52:34.817
CHERYL:
      All right, you guys.

52:34.819 --> 52:37.153
I got the tickets.
         Everyone ready?

52:37.155 --> 52:39.555
-Yes.
              -No.

52:39.557 --> 52:42.892
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

52:50.234 --> 52:52.468
-Which way?
           -This way.

52:52.470 --> 52:55.337
[ Screaming in distance ]

52:55.339 --> 52:56.672
CHERYL:
              Greg!

52:58.242 --> 53:00.176
JONNY:
 Who the hell are these people?

53:00.178 --> 53:02.378
Oh, man. They look like
    they're on a shitty date.

53:02.380 --> 53:04.280
[ Laughter ]

53:04.282 --> 53:06.415
TROY: They're having
       a rough time, man.

53:06.417 --> 53:08.517
Hey, how you doing?
You guys on a date or something?

53:08.519 --> 53:11.253
Let's go.
     [ Grunting ] Oh, shit.

53:11.255 --> 53:14.256
Here we go. All right, boys.
    You know the plan, right?

53:14.258 --> 53:16.692
Same thing.
     Ready to rock 'n' roll?

53:16.694 --> 53:18.527
Okay. You walk around the thing.
        You get in there.

53:18.529 --> 53:20.229
-Five on five. Got it?
     -We got it.

53:20.231 --> 53:22.665
Let's go. Come on. Come on.
      Let's go. Go, go, go.

53:22.667 --> 53:25.267
[ Insects chirping ]

53:25.269 --> 53:27.770
[ Indistinct conversations
          in distance ]

53:31.742 --> 53:33.776
Oh, hey, Mr. Talbott.

53:33.778 --> 53:35.611
-Troy.
          -One, please.

53:35.613 --> 53:38.747
One?
        Oh, that's great.

53:38.749 --> 53:41.250
Troy, got to tell you,
    I'm pleasantly surprised

53:41.252 --> 53:44.420
to see you here without all your
    emotional support animals

53:44.422 --> 53:45.921
that you call friends.

53:45.923 --> 53:49.558
Could it be
  you are actually growing up,

53:49.560 --> 53:51.527
leaving high school behind?

53:51.529 --> 53:53.796
I graduated four years ago,
             but...

53:54.365 --> 53:55.864
I hadn't noticed.

53:55.866 --> 53:57.266
Here.

53:57.268 --> 53:59.668
Have yourself a mask.

54:00.338 --> 54:01.870
All the kids have them.

54:05.876 --> 54:07.443
Good seeing you, Mr. T.

54:07.812 --> 54:09.545
-You too, Troy.
         -Mm-hmm.

54:09.547 --> 54:11.847
-Thanks for coming.
       -Any time.

54:13.784 --> 54:16.318
[ Suspenseful music playing ]

54:34.472 --> 54:37.473
[ Shouting, screaming
          in distance ]

54:42.046 --> 54:43.579
Hey, Sheriff.
          It's Reddick.

54:43.581 --> 54:46.282
I have eyes on Denver's
         missing wheels.

54:46.284 --> 54:48.017
[ Whistling ]

54:48.019 --> 54:50.319
[ Siren wailing ]

54:50.888 --> 54:52.921
Copy that, Iris.
      What's your location?

54:52.923 --> 54:56.592
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

54:56.594 --> 54:58.527
Deputy Reddick,
        location, please.

55:04.935 --> 55:08.370
REDDICK: I'm at the church,
in pursuit of potential suspect.

55:10.341 --> 55:12.941
[ Indistinct conversation ]

55:15.079 --> 55:17.913
JAYNE: Reddick, do not pursue
         without backup.

55:19.450 --> 55:21.550
[ Music continues ]

55:28.359 --> 55:31.493
-REDDICK: Copy that, Sheriff.
  -[ Static ]

55:31.495 --> 55:32.528
Come back, Reddick.

55:32.530 --> 55:34.430
Deputy Reddick.

55:34.432 --> 55:36.365
Reddick, report.

55:36.367 --> 55:37.966
-It's starting.
         -JAYNE: Shit.

55:40.104 --> 55:42.905
[ Engine revs ]

55:42.907 --> 55:45.607
[ Audience shouting, cheering
          in distance ]

55:48.679 --> 55:51.113
-Hey, shitheads. Get in here.
  -Freezing as fuck, dude.

55:51.115 --> 55:53.515
Looked like old man Talbott
   scared the shit out of you.

55:53.517 --> 55:55.017
Talbott doesn't scare anyone,
              bro.

55:55.019 --> 55:56.518
-You kidding me? Oh, yeah?
   -What you talking about?

55:56.520 --> 55:57.653
-You're a tough guy, huh?
    -Yeah, hit me, man.

55:57.655 --> 55:59.588
I'll throw you down the st--

55:59.590 --> 56:01.123
JONNY:
            Oh, fuck.

56:01.125 --> 56:03.525
Tell you what, Mr. Troy.

56:03.527 --> 56:07.129
You and your shithead five
   can make a healthy donation

56:07.131 --> 56:08.897
to tonight's cause,

56:08.899 --> 56:12.468
or I can call
    that nice Deputy Reddick,

56:12.470 --> 56:13.869
and she can read you
          your rights.

56:13.871 --> 56:16.138
What do you think?

56:16.140 --> 56:18.073
-Uh...
            -Pay up.

56:21.746 --> 56:24.413
Get it out. Get it out.
            Hurry up.

56:24.415 --> 56:25.748
GREG:
       This isn't so bad.

56:25.750 --> 56:28.117
Are you insane?
       I can't stand this.

56:28.119 --> 56:29.518
Can't stand what?

56:29.520 --> 56:31.620
You haven't opened your eyes
            since --

56:31.622 --> 56:34.556
-[ Clown laughing ]
       -[ Screams ]

56:39.130 --> 56:42.131
[ Laughter ]

56:42.133 --> 56:43.966
GREG:
    Maybe we should go back.

56:43.968 --> 56:45.734
I thought you wanted to
           be scared.

56:45.736 --> 56:48.036
-[ Chain saw revving ]
     -[ Screaming ]

56:48.038 --> 56:50.105
[ Growls ]

57:03.687 --> 57:05.621
I don't want to be here anymore!

57:07.591 --> 57:09.591
-Here. Help her. I'll get him.
 -I want to go!

57:09.593 --> 57:11.093
-I want to go!
 -NICKY: What about your candy?

57:11.095 --> 57:14.630
I don't care about the candy!
          I want to go!

57:14.632 --> 57:17.032
[ Chain saw revving ]

57:17.034 --> 57:20.102
[ Growls ]

57:20.104 --> 57:23.138
[ Thunder rumbling ]

57:26.043 --> 57:29.178
JOHNNY: There's not much sense
     in my going to church.

57:29.180 --> 57:31.079
TROY:
    God, this movie's boring.

57:31.081 --> 57:32.815
-Give me some colors.
      -Are you serious?

57:32.817 --> 57:34.883
I knew we should've gone
    in the goddamn maze, man.

57:34.885 --> 57:36.785
-Yeah. Fuck that.
 -It would've been way more fun.

57:36.787 --> 57:38.554
Me and the cool kids over here
         are gonna go...

57:38.556 --> 57:40.055
Man, you are
      such a little bitch.

57:40.057 --> 57:41.824
TROY: You guys want to go out
      to the fucking maze?

57:41.826 --> 57:44.626
-No, no -- Really?
  -Better than this shit show.

57:44.628 --> 57:46.028
You'll be all right.

57:46.030 --> 57:48.096
Yeah. No, no. No hard feelings.
          That's fine.

57:48.098 --> 57:50.065
-TROY: See you later, man.
 -We'll see you later, pumpkin.

57:50.067 --> 57:52.968
Enjoy the fun
     in this piece of shit.

57:52.970 --> 57:55.737
BARBRA: Stop it.
   You're acting like a child!

57:55.739 --> 57:57.873
JOHNNY:
     They're coming for you.

57:57.875 --> 58:00.108
Look!
  There comes one of them now.

58:00.110 --> 58:01.944
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

58:01.946 --> 58:04.646
[ Siren wails, stops ]

58:16.060 --> 58:18.494
[ Door opens ]

58:18.496 --> 58:21.263
-Denver, Sheriff.
        -JAYNE: Hey.

58:21.265 --> 58:24.266
Quite a posse you've got going,
 but the first movie's started.

58:24.268 --> 58:25.968
You seen Reddick?

58:25.970 --> 58:29.538
Yeah. She went around back
       to check the maze.

58:29.540 --> 58:30.839
Wan, Slater, take the street.

58:30.841 --> 58:32.174
Denver, let's check
          the cemetery.

58:32.176 --> 58:35.110
-Something wrong?
        -Just be careful.

58:36.680 --> 58:38.580
Okay.

58:38.582 --> 58:41.283
Get my shotgun is what <i> I'll</i> do.

58:41.285 --> 58:42.584
Just got to wait for --

58:42.586 --> 58:44.219
-Greg, wait!
          -[ Gasps ]

58:47.525 --> 58:49.858
What's wrong?
     Did you hurt yourself?

58:49.860 --> 58:52.861
[ Laughter in distance ]

58:52.863 --> 58:55.264
[ Dramatic music plays ]

58:57.067 --> 58:59.601
[ Scoffs ]
      Greg, it's the clown.

58:59.603 --> 59:01.003
Different clothes.

59:01.005 --> 59:02.738
Then it's a different clown.

59:02.740 --> 59:05.073
He has a knife.

59:06.777 --> 59:09.878
It's fake, Greg.
      Look. He works here.

59:09.880 --> 59:11.813
You're wrong.

59:12.883 --> 59:15.684
Stay here.
         I'll show you.

59:15.686 --> 59:18.687
No!
             Don't!

59:18.689 --> 59:21.823
[ Music continues ]

59:21.825 --> 59:23.959
[ Cat screeching in distance ]

59:28.933 --> 59:31.333
You're scaring the boy.

59:35.172 --> 59:37.139
It's okay, Greg.

59:37.141 --> 59:39.274
He's gonna let us pass.

59:41.912 --> 59:43.912
Hey! Hey!

59:43.914 --> 59:45.180
Greg! Wait!

59:45.182 --> 59:48.083
There's nothing to be afraid of.

59:48.085 --> 59:49.985
Greg!

59:49.987 --> 59:51.787
[ Gasps ]

59:54.992 --> 59:57.225
[ Music continues ]

59:57.227 --> 59:58.794
CHERYL:
         See? He's gone.

59:59.630 --> 01:00:00.996
Come on.

01:00:08.138 --> 01:00:10.739
[ Dramatic music plays ]

01:00:17.181 --> 01:00:18.647
Come on.
            Come on.

01:00:18.649 --> 01:00:20.048
Oh, my God.

01:00:20.050 --> 01:00:22.317
[ Screams ]

01:00:22.319 --> 01:00:24.286
There's Greg.

01:00:24.922 --> 01:00:27.089
It's Trick, Nicky.
   We got to get out of here.

01:00:27.091 --> 01:00:29.157
You've been drinking
        Greg's Kool-Aid?

01:00:29.159 --> 01:00:30.192
[ Growling ]

01:00:30.194 --> 01:00:32.194
-Fuck off!
           -[ Grunts ]

01:00:32.196 --> 01:00:35.731
Oh, my nose.
 Oh, I think she broke my nose.

01:00:35.733 --> 01:00:38.967
[ Dramatic music plays ]

01:00:39.903 --> 01:00:42.704
-No. Let's go back.
      -This is the way out.

01:00:42.706 --> 01:00:44.640
It's just around him.
       We're almost there.

01:00:44.642 --> 01:00:47.142
[ Chain saw revving ]

01:00:57.287 --> 01:00:59.755
[ Grunting ]

01:00:59.757 --> 01:01:01.823
[ Dramatic music plays ]

01:01:06.263 --> 01:01:07.295
Trick.

01:01:09.199 --> 01:01:10.932
-Run! Run!
         -[ Whimpering ]

01:01:10.934 --> 01:01:12.934
[ Up-tempo music plays ]

01:01:15.406 --> 01:01:18.073
[ Screaming in distance ]

01:01:18.809 --> 01:01:20.709
DENVER:
          What's that?

01:01:20.711 --> 01:01:23.345
[ Static on radio ]

01:01:23.347 --> 01:01:24.446
Oh, shit.

01:01:30.788 --> 01:01:32.821
[ Dramatic music plays ]

01:01:33.824 --> 01:01:35.223
It's Trick.

01:01:35.225 --> 01:01:37.092
Moviegoers at the church,
      families in the maze.

01:01:37.094 --> 01:01:39.161
It's like a killing ground.
      We got to warn them.

01:01:39.163 --> 01:01:41.430
Wan, Slater, we found Reddick's
    body in the fire escape.

01:01:41.432 --> 01:01:43.732
Call it in.
          Denver, wait!

01:01:43.734 --> 01:01:45.467
I need bodies
     to lock down the church

01:01:45.469 --> 01:01:48.737
and the crime scene
     around Reddick -- now!

01:01:52.276 --> 01:01:54.342
[ Dramatic music plays ]

01:02:11.261 --> 01:02:14.029
[ Crowd screaming, gasping ]

01:02:30.180 --> 01:02:32.147
MAN:
         Wait up, guys!

01:02:33.283 --> 01:02:34.850
[ Laughing ]

01:02:34.852 --> 01:02:36.952
[ Grunts ]

01:02:39.757 --> 01:02:41.289
Get out of here!

01:02:41.291 --> 01:02:44.259
Tell everybody you see to go.
     There's been a murder.

01:02:51.535 --> 01:02:54.770
[ Hinges creaking ]

01:03:02.546 --> 01:03:04.412
[ Footsteps approaching ]

01:03:04.414 --> 01:03:06.114
Sheriff, it's me.

01:03:06.116 --> 01:03:08.450
Jesus, Slater.
           Stay here.

01:03:08.452 --> 01:03:10.051
Alone?

01:03:10.053 --> 01:03:11.853
Keep it together, Slater.

01:03:11.855 --> 01:03:15.490
[ Indistinct conversations,
   siren wailing in distance ]

01:03:17.828 --> 01:03:20.395
[ Breathing heavily ]
    Sweetie, you got to run.

01:03:20.397 --> 01:03:21.897
I can't carry you anymore!

01:03:21.899 --> 01:03:24.232
-No! I can't! I'm scared!
    -It's okay.

01:03:24.234 --> 01:03:26.034
CHERYL:
           Greg, wait!

01:03:26.036 --> 01:03:28.470
-NICKY: Greg!
     -It's Trick! He's here.

01:03:28.472 --> 01:03:30.272
Greg!
         [ Whimpering ]

01:03:30.274 --> 01:03:32.140
-[ Dramatic music plays ]
    -Nicky!

01:03:32.142 --> 01:03:33.508
-[ Gun cocks ]
         -Get down!

01:03:38.315 --> 01:03:41.016
[ Breathing heavily ]

01:03:42.419 --> 01:03:46.054
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

01:03:46.056 --> 01:03:48.523
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:03:48.525 --> 01:03:49.891
Human after all.

01:03:51.461 --> 01:03:52.828
Denver.

01:03:54.198 --> 01:03:55.497
DENVER:
            Come on.

01:03:55.499 --> 01:03:58.233
[ Gun cocks ]

01:03:58.235 --> 01:04:01.236
[ Footsteps approaching ]

01:04:07.177 --> 01:04:08.443
[ Exhales sharply ]
            Fuck me.

01:04:08.445 --> 01:04:11.179
-Shit!
  -I could've killed you, Tal.

01:04:11.181 --> 01:04:13.315
That makes two of us, Sheriff.

01:04:13.317 --> 01:04:14.850
What the hell is going on?

01:04:15.319 --> 01:04:18.286
Look, we've got trouble.

01:04:18.288 --> 01:04:20.088
Deputy Reddick is dead.

01:04:21.058 --> 01:04:22.357
Iris?

01:04:22.359 --> 01:04:24.192
I need to lock down the church.

01:04:24.194 --> 01:04:27.529
Any one of your costumed
 moviegoers could be her killer.

01:04:27.531 --> 01:04:30.232
Is it him -- Trick Weaver?

01:04:30.901 --> 01:04:32.534
I think so, Tal.

01:04:34.037 --> 01:04:37.305
Let's go find
      that little sumbitch.

01:04:41.245 --> 01:04:43.111
Let's take a look at that arm.

01:04:43.113 --> 01:04:45.413
[ Indistinct shouting
          in distance ]

01:04:53.390 --> 01:04:56.024
[ Grunts ]

01:04:59.029 --> 01:05:01.096
Could've been worse.
         You got lucky.

01:05:01.098 --> 01:05:03.632
I don't <i> feel</i> lucky.

01:05:04.234 --> 01:05:05.533
[ Whimpers ]

01:05:05.535 --> 01:05:08.069
[ Laughter,
      indistinct shouting ]

01:05:08.071 --> 01:05:09.604
-There we go!
         -CHERYL: Troy!

01:05:09.606 --> 01:05:11.373
Troy!

01:05:11.375 --> 01:05:12.440
Trick Weaver's back.

01:05:12.442 --> 01:05:14.342
Oh. Hey, Cheryl.
              What?

01:05:14.344 --> 01:05:16.511
CHERYL:
      Trick Weaver is back.

01:05:16.513 --> 01:05:17.646
Trick?

01:05:17.648 --> 01:05:19.414
MAN:
         Troy, come on!

01:05:21.451 --> 01:05:23.218
Hey, yo!
            Wait up!

01:05:23.220 --> 01:05:27.088
-Let's get out of here.
  -Yeah, let's get out of here.

01:05:27.457 --> 01:05:29.324
Come on.

01:05:29.326 --> 01:05:30.558
Come on.
              Okay.

01:05:30.560 --> 01:05:32.594
[ Dramatic music playing ]

01:05:35.365 --> 01:05:38.166
Deputies are on their way.
      Shut down the movie.

01:05:38.168 --> 01:05:40.268
The last thing I want
   is Trick taking a hostage,

01:05:40.270 --> 01:05:41.269
so go easy.

01:05:41.271 --> 01:05:43.138
I always go easy.

01:05:43.140 --> 01:05:44.639
No, you don't.

01:05:50.647 --> 01:05:52.414
All right.
         Come on, guys.

01:05:53.583 --> 01:05:55.317
Everybody hurry up.

01:05:55.319 --> 01:05:57.385
[ Screaming in distance ]

01:05:57.387 --> 01:05:59.487
Everyone get in.

01:06:02.025 --> 01:06:04.326
-Get them to the hospital.
   -Okay.

01:06:06.263 --> 01:06:08.096
Detective Den--

01:06:08.098 --> 01:06:10.532
Mike...kill him this time.

01:06:12.336 --> 01:06:15.370
[ Dramatic music playing ]

01:06:17.374 --> 01:06:19.074
[ Gun cocks ]

01:06:25.582 --> 01:06:27.282
Got your ass now, Trick.

01:06:27.284 --> 01:06:30.051
I'm coming for you,
       you son of a bitch!

01:06:30.053 --> 01:06:32.053
[ Music continues ]

01:06:37.461 --> 01:06:39.327
[ Whistling ]

01:06:40.764 --> 01:06:43.064
[ Gunshot echoing ]

01:06:43.467 --> 01:06:45.200
Everybody down!

01:06:45.202 --> 01:06:47.002
[ Audience murmuring ]

01:06:47.004 --> 01:06:49.170
BEN:
Well, if you're coming, come on.

01:06:49.639 --> 01:06:52.173
-[ Knife thuds ]
        -Get in.

01:06:52.175 --> 01:06:54.409
[ Dramatic music plays ]

01:06:54.411 --> 01:06:56.578
[ Gasping ]

01:06:59.383 --> 01:07:01.750
[ Weakly ]
            Sumbitch.

01:07:06.490 --> 01:07:09.024
[ Music continues ]

01:07:09.026 --> 01:07:12.027
[ Crowd screams ]

01:07:24.074 --> 01:07:26.041
Aah!

01:07:31.214 --> 01:07:32.747
JAYNE: What are you doing?
          Go after him.

01:07:32.749 --> 01:07:34.616
Not without you.
            Come on.

01:07:38.755 --> 01:07:41.656
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

01:07:41.658 --> 01:07:42.057
Slater.

01:07:46.596 --> 01:07:48.663
-Call it in.
      -Sheriff, we saw him.

01:07:48.665 --> 01:07:50.432
He's headed back into the maze.

01:07:50.434 --> 01:07:52.233
Copy that.
        We're on our way.

01:07:52.235 --> 01:07:54.369
Secure the church.
         Check everyone.

01:07:54.371 --> 01:07:55.703
Let's go!

01:07:58.208 --> 01:08:00.175
DENVER:
   Troy Meeks is in the maze.

01:08:00.177 --> 01:08:02.177
JAYNE: There's lots of people
    still in the maze, Mike.

01:08:02.179 --> 01:08:04.746
But Troy's the only one
 who stabbed him four years ago.

01:08:04.748 --> 01:08:06.414
You think he's here for Troy?

01:08:06.416 --> 01:08:07.816
He here's for anyone
       who slighted him --

01:08:07.818 --> 01:08:10.652
you, me, Troy, Talbott --
    and anyone we care about.

01:08:10.654 --> 01:08:14.322
[ Dramatic music playing ]

01:08:19.429 --> 01:08:22.296
[ Indistinct talking on P.A. ]

01:08:24.600 --> 01:08:27.368
MAN ON P.A.:
 ...everyone leave the maze now.

01:08:27.370 --> 01:08:29.537
Hey, had a little too much,
            pig boy?

01:08:29.538 --> 01:08:30.772
You up, man?

01:08:30.774 --> 01:08:32.640
Piggy went to the market.

01:08:32.642 --> 01:08:34.709
Yo.
        Be ready, dudes.

01:08:34.711 --> 01:08:37.312
He's gonna jump up
 at any moment, I'm telling you.

01:08:37.314 --> 01:08:39.613
Troy, you got to come with us.

01:08:39.616 --> 01:08:40.715
Hey. Yo.

01:08:43.620 --> 01:08:46.187
Whoa. That -- That was there.
 We were just -- We were just...

01:08:46.189 --> 01:08:47.822
He's dead.

01:08:47.823 --> 01:08:49.357
What?

01:08:49.359 --> 01:08:50.658
Trick Weaver's back.

01:08:52.395 --> 01:08:53.895
No.

01:08:53.897 --> 01:08:56.531
I mean, no way.
          Trick's dead.

01:08:56.533 --> 01:08:57.765
He's not dead.
           He's here.

01:08:57.767 --> 01:08:59.167
And we think he's here for you.

01:08:59.169 --> 01:09:00.835
Me?
            W-Why me?

01:09:00.837 --> 01:09:02.670
You stabbed him four years ago.

01:09:02.671 --> 01:09:04.572
But I...

01:09:06.609 --> 01:09:08.443
Trick doesn't think that,
            does he?

01:09:09.179 --> 01:09:11.246
Why <i> wouldn't</i> he think that?

01:09:14.251 --> 01:09:16.651
'Cause, uh...

01:09:19.756 --> 01:09:23.457
'Cause I...
     I didn't really do it.

01:09:25.194 --> 01:09:26.728
See, I-I mean,
    I didn't even punch him.

01:09:26.729 --> 01:09:28.662
That was Dan and the other guys.
          I was just --

01:09:28.665 --> 01:09:30.497
You stabbed him
      with that fire poker.

01:09:30.500 --> 01:09:32.433
Troy, that's what you told us.

01:09:32.435 --> 01:09:34.702
Right, but...
 s-she didn't remember doing it.

01:09:34.703 --> 01:09:37.272
She was in shock, see?

01:09:37.274 --> 01:09:39.607
I just figured
  since she didn't remember...

01:09:39.609 --> 01:09:43.310
that maybe I should tell
      everybody it was me.

01:09:44.781 --> 01:09:45.779
For her sake, I mean.

01:09:45.782 --> 01:09:48.515
Who didn't remember?

01:09:51.254 --> 01:09:52.953
Cheryl stabbed Trick
        with that poker.

01:09:52.956 --> 01:09:54.556
He saw her do it, too.

01:09:55.425 --> 01:09:56.791
The hospital.

01:09:56.793 --> 01:09:59.394
You don't think he really
    wants to hurt <i> me,</i> do you?

01:09:59.396 --> 01:10:00.628
Hey, what about me?!

01:10:00.630 --> 01:10:02.530
Am I -- Am I gonna live?!

01:10:03.900 --> 01:10:05.500
WOMAN:
         Nicole Taylor?

01:10:05.502 --> 01:10:09.537
[ Indistinct talking on P.A. ]

01:10:14.244 --> 01:10:16.377
Hey, I'm gonna go check
           on my dad.

01:10:16.379 --> 01:10:18.213
Of course.
         We'll be here.

01:10:18.215 --> 01:10:19.514
Okay.

01:10:21.218 --> 01:10:23.251
[ Keypad beeping ]

01:10:30.694 --> 01:10:32.860
I'll be back, kiddo.

01:10:35.232 --> 01:10:37.665
NICKY: Mom and Dad
    will be here soon, okay?

01:10:47.244 --> 01:10:49.811
I remember the day Mom left.

01:10:51.815 --> 01:10:56.718
You asked me...if I thought
      you were a good dad.

01:11:04.294 --> 01:11:06.628
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

01:11:07.897 --> 01:11:12.634
Well...I wish I could
      tell you that, but...

01:11:13.803 --> 01:11:15.870
I know things were bad
         after Mom left,

01:11:15.872 --> 01:11:19.741
but...she didn't just leave you.

01:11:20.343 --> 01:11:22.510
She left me too.

01:11:24.381 --> 01:11:27.048
Why are you doing this to me?
           [ Sniffs ]

01:11:27.050 --> 01:11:28.916
I need you, Daddy.

01:11:28.918 --> 01:11:33.321
I-I'm alone, and...I don't know
  what I would do without you.

01:11:33.323 --> 01:11:35.490
[ Sobs ]

01:11:35.992 --> 01:11:38.026
I'm sorry.

01:11:39.896 --> 01:11:41.863
[ Whispering ]
           I'm sorry.

01:11:42.465 --> 01:11:43.898
I wish...

01:11:43.900 --> 01:11:48.403
I wish there was something
            I can do.

01:11:50.340 --> 01:11:53.641
But if -- if you want to know...

01:11:57.714 --> 01:11:59.881
[ Sniffs ]

01:12:02.452 --> 01:12:05.687
...you've been the best dad
      I could ever ask for.

01:12:07.791 --> 01:12:09.424
I love you.

01:12:09.426 --> 01:12:11.526
[ Static hisses ]

01:12:11.528 --> 01:12:14.028
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

01:12:22.505 --> 01:12:25.106
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

01:12:33.650 --> 01:12:35.550
No. No. No.

01:12:36.686 --> 01:12:38.886
No. No.

01:12:38.888 --> 01:12:40.655
No, no, no, no, no, no.

01:12:40.657 --> 01:12:43.524
[ Sobbing ]
       No, no, no, no, no.

01:12:45.962 --> 01:12:48.029
No.

01:12:48.031 --> 01:12:50.031
[ Gasps ] No.

01:12:50.033 --> 01:12:52.033
Dad. Oh, Daddy.

01:12:52.035 --> 01:12:54.769
[ Sobs ]

01:12:54.771 --> 01:12:57.405
I'm so sorry.

01:13:02.479 --> 01:13:05.012
[ Exhales sharply ]

01:13:05.014 --> 01:13:07.014
[ Screaming ]

01:13:09.686 --> 01:13:12.153
[ Dramatic music plays ]

01:13:18.027 --> 01:13:19.427
MAN:
      The power's been cut!

01:13:19.429 --> 01:13:20.795
-Emergency lights?
       -They're out.

01:13:20.797 --> 01:13:22.830
-What the hell?
   -DR. STEVE: What happened?

01:13:22.832 --> 01:13:24.766
JAYNE:
           I-I'm fine.

01:13:24.768 --> 01:13:26.501
-I'll find Cheryl.
    -She'll be with her dad.

01:13:26.503 --> 01:13:28.503
-[ Gasping ]
          -Helen!

01:13:28.505 --> 01:13:29.537
[ Weakly ]
            Help me.

01:13:29.539 --> 01:13:30.805
Lock down the E.R.

01:13:30.807 --> 01:13:33.007
-I'll come with you.
      -Wait here.

01:13:33.009 --> 01:13:36.511
DENVER: Mitch, we need a
 perimeter around the E.R., now!

01:13:36.513 --> 01:13:38.980
All right, Sheriff.
    Let's get you stitched --

01:13:38.982 --> 01:13:40.882
Sheriff?

01:13:41.551 --> 01:13:42.917
Nurse?
            Code red!

01:13:43.987 --> 01:13:45.453
What if we're too late?

01:13:45.455 --> 01:13:47.088
Slater, keep it together.

01:13:47.090 --> 01:13:49.023
How?
  How am I supposed to do that?

01:13:49.025 --> 01:13:50.558
He's always a step ahead of us.

01:13:50.560 --> 01:13:52.760
It's not normal.
         It's not human.

01:13:52.762 --> 01:13:54.929
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

01:14:06.209 --> 01:14:09.677
Hey. You're injured.
    You should be in the E.R.

01:14:09.679 --> 01:14:14.182
Cheryl, you, me --
      That's what he wants.

01:14:15.518 --> 01:14:17.919
That's why he's doing this.

01:14:18.888 --> 01:14:22.089
Do us all a favor.
   Don't make it easy for him.

